Error is thrown if date type is strict_date_optional_time_nanos and ingested data has single digit nanoseconds. I get the same error when the type is `date_nanos`, too. 
```
PUT test-date
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "datetest-nano": {
        "type": "date",
        "format": "strict_date_optional_time_nanos"
      }
    }
  }
}

POST test-date/_doc/123
{
  "datetest-nano": "2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z"
}
=>
{
  "error" : {
    "root_cause" : [
      {
        "type" : "mapper_parsing_exception",
        "reason" : "failed to parse field [datetest-nano] of type [date] in document with id '123'. Preview of field's value: '2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z'"
      }
    ],
    "type" : "mapper_parsing_exception",
    "reason" : "failed to parse field [datetest-nano] of type [date] in document with id '123'. Preview of field's value: '2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z'",
    "caused_by" : {
      "type" : "illegal_argument_exception",
      "reason" : "failed to parse date field [2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z] with format [strict_date_optional_time_nanos]",
      "caused_by" : {
        "type" : "date_time_parse_exception",
        "reason" : "Text '2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z' could not be parsed, unparsed text found at index 19"
      }
    }
  },
  "status" : 400
}
```
I heard this is not a bug, since the code does enforce a minimum 3 digits nano value.
However, `strict_date_optional_time` allow one digit fraction of a second part as below:
```
PUT test-date
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "datetest-nano": {
        "type": "date",
        "format": "strict_date_optional_time"
      }
    }
  }
}

POST test-date/_doc/123
{
  "datetest-nano": "2020-06-19T07:16:17.2Z"
} 
=>
{
  "_index" : "test-date",
  "_type" : "_doc",
  "_id" : "123",
  "_version" : 1,
  "result" : "created",
  "_shards" : {
    "total" : 2,
    "successful" : 1,
    "failed" : 0
  },
  "_seq_no" : 0,
  "_primary_term" : 1
}
```

I think either 1) `strict_date_optional_time_nanos` should allow 1 digit nano value or 2) the documentation should mention that `strict_date_optional_time_nanos` requires a minimum 3 digit nano value while "strict_date_optional_time" allows 1 digit millisecond value.

**Elasticsearch version** (`bin/elasticsearch --version`): 7.6.2, 7.9.0

